-- LC Waikiki, Turkey’s Top Apparel Seller, Sees 29% Sales Growth
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-07-30T11:00:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-30/lc-waikiki-turkey-s-top-apparel-seller-sees-29-sales-growth.html
LC Waikiki,  Turkey ’s biggest ready-
to-wear retailer, aims to increase sales 29 percent to 3.75
billion liras ($2.1 billion) this year as it opens stores
outside Turkey.  The retailer, owned by Taha Group of Turkey, plans to
increase the number of its stores abroad to 200 by 2015 from 36
by entering new markets such as Georgia,  Saudi Arabia , Iran,
Morocco and Azerbaijan, the Istanbul-based company said in an e-
mailed statement.  LC Waikiki, which plans to have 450 stores in Turkey by
2015 compared to 373 now, is the biggest retailer by sales,
according to a survey by market researcher Ipsos KMG, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
